    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So I guess the first question is: Where do I get the Python version information from ?\nFrom IPEP17:\n`kernel_info`: an object containing information about the kernel that the notebook should be run with (see also IPEP 13. It should include the following keys:\n-  `name`: the name of the kernel specification\n-  `language`: the language that the kernel runs\n-  `codemirror_mode`: (optional) the codemirror mode to use when displaying the notebook\n\nSo `codemirror_mode` should not be used as you said. `language` is used right now and does not give you version information and `name` will give you `python3` but to use this key seems more like a side effect. Do we need an additional `version` key ?\n"
  },
