    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I was travelling the last days, so I had not much chance to look at it.\n\nActually, I don't understand your code:\nYou have a `language` attribute in `['metadata']['kernelspec']`, hardcode it to `python` in `kernlespec.py`, but never use it. \nIn `exporter.py` you look for `nb['metadata']['language']` that doesn't exist.\nIn `highlight.py` you fallback to `ipython` as language name.\n\nAdding things to code I don't understand is hard. It would be nice if you could take a look at it.\nOtherwise, adding somethin like `' pygments_lexer'  : 'python%d'` to kernelspec would be easy to do.\n"
  },
