    "updated_at": "2014-10-16T20:54:07Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "OK, I'm happy to work on this. If you're interested:\n- The `language` key in kernelspecs is intended as a fallback for things like syntax highlighters that don't have an explicit key. We use codemirror for highlighting in the live notebook, and pygments for higlighting in nbconvert, and these have specific keys, but if you wanted to use another tool to highlight it, or maybe do some kind of static analysis, it could use the language key.\n- The language field in metadata is used by some other kernels with IPython 2, before we added kernelspecs. I think IJulia uses it. Once IPython 3 is out, hopefully scripts will appear to turn that into proper kernelspec metadata.\n- `highlight.py`: this code was presumably written before we knew exactly how supporting different languages would work.\n"
  },
